My passion comic since I know someone would change my characters stories.

I used to write a lot of stories from 5th grade up to about freshman year. Granted my ex mostly wrote with me but a lot of my stories were written by myself since he and I would always kind of argue over where the story should go. Kinda why I never have a team helping me with

I used to be extremely into writing but I've always (and still) struggle with some punctuation. Mostly I tend to favor commas that are just littered throughout my stories as a way to break up my run on sentences which isn't the proper way ;v;
What keeps them going? That sorta thing, believe me it helps a lot when developing a chara's storyline as well as how the characters around them will ultimately effect and change said character

Bit of writer advice, when writing your charas stories you need to put yourself in that character's shoes. Live their life in that moment, feel how they feel, what are their dreams? What are their goals?
